label intro_poem:

    show bg black with Dissolve(2.0)
    show text "For every defining moment, there is a Before and an After." with Dissolve(1.0)
    pause(4.5)
    hide text with Dissolve(2.0)
    show text "The Before is an open sea. \nEvery turn of the rudder in water, every breath of the wind in the sail, \nholds equal promise of propelling a craft onward and dragging it under." with Dissolve(2.0)
    pause(9.0)
    hide text with Dissolve(2.5)
    show text "The After is a rearview mirror. \nThe rubble is already on the ground and growing ever smaller in the lens. \nThe only control is the speed of onward acceleration." with Dissolve(2.0)
    pause(9.0)
    hide text with Dissolve(2.5)
    show text "But what can be said of the moment itself, \nthis impossibly thin waist in the hourglass of time?" with Dissolve(1.0)
    pause(5.0)
    hide text with Dissolve(0.75)
    show text "What can be said of this paradoxical well of space, \nwhere even the falling seconds dare to defy gravity?" with Dissolve(1.0)
    pause(6.0)
    hide text with Dissolve(1.0)
    show text "What dare we make of it?" with Dissolve(1.5)
    pause(5.0)
    hide text with Dissolve(2.0)
    pause(3.0)

    stop music fadeout 3.5
    pause (2.0)

    jump office
